Project: Kaya Skincare — Marketing Performance Dashboard

The problem
A D2C skincare brand was spending ₹3L/month across Meta, Google, and influencers with no unified view of what was actually working. Their monthly reports came from three separate tools, took the founder 6 hours to compile, and arrived 10 days after month-end — by which point the insights were already stale. They suspected some campaigns were bleeding money but couldn't prove which ones.

What I built
I pulled their Meta Ads, Google Ads, and Shopify data into a single Power BI model with blended ROAS and CAC calculated across all channels. The dashboard refreshes daily and surfaces not just the numbers, but the decisions — underperforming campaigns are automatically flagged when ROAS drops below 1.0, with estimated wasted spend called out at the top. The founder now opens this dashboard every Monday instead of waiting for a monthly PDF.

The outcome
Within the first 30 days, we identified ₹47,200 in spend across 4 campaigns running below break-even. Pausing them and reallocating to the top 3 performers (Google brand search, Meta retargeting, and skincare-creator influencers) moved blended ROAS from 2.1x to 3.4x. Monthly reporting time dropped from 6 hours to 10 minutes. CAC fell from ₹508 to ₹412.


